The paper presents a distributed asynchronous algorithm for approximating a single component of the solution to a system of linear equations, which is a problem that falls under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and scientific computing (cs.SI). The algorithm is based on residual updates, which is a technique commonly used in distributed systems and parallel computing, and thus the paper may also be relevant to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper analyzes the algorithm in the context of a cloud computation model, which involves large-scale data processing and machine learning, and thus may also be relevant to the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
